High-resolution input images are priced as follows: 
- 85 base tokens are used each time
- For smaller images, the image is divided into 512x512 pixel tiles
- For larger images, the image will be resized so that a maximum of 4 tiles will be used
- 170 tokens are used per tile
- The standard price per input token is used for the total number of tokens required (for this model, this is $2.5/million input tokens)
Example: a 512x513 pixel input image:
Tokens = 85 + 170*2
